result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer]. The defendant was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer] was dismissed by the court.

  • Otilio Nmi Olivares Benitez was found guilty of OWI (5th or 6th) [Modifiers: Alcohol Fine Enhancer], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
DA Response on Petition for Sentence Adjustment  
  **Reviewed by Judge Melvin on 11-12-2020:  I have reviewed the petition, the DA's objection and the orgainl sentencing documents. I am not willing to modify the sentence. I am very glad to hear he has a plan to get into the trades upon release, and also that he has been working with religious programs while at Jackson Correctional. However, I am not willing to release the defendant early. The sentence was appropriate, he has given him self the tools for success, and for that he should be commended.**

District Attorney's Office Law Intern Brook Erickson, assisted by ADA Woller, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Patrick Ryan appeared as interpreter.  Ms. Erickson presents the offer.  Atty. Court orders Count 2 dismissed and read in and Count 3 dismissed by operation of law.  Court also ordered case 14CF1046 dismissed and read into this case.  Ms. Erickson presents her recommendations for sentencing.  Atty. Luening presents his recommendations for sentencing.  Court orders the defendant be returned to Jackson Correctional.

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

COUNT 1:

IMPOSED SENTENCE OF:   

4 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (Concurrent to defendant's current sentence)
  -  2 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION. 


Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

IGNITION INTERLOCK: 36 months.

AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;

Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling as recommended by the Agent.

No operation of a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license.

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $24.00 (to be paid from prison wages and/or as a condition of extended supervision - to be forward to City of Brookfield Police Department);

FINE:  $12,183.00 (to be paid from prison wages and/or to be paid as a condition of extended supervision or any prison monies per statute);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
